{% extends "layouts/doc-layout" %}

{% block title %}Downcase Filter - Wisp Template Documentation{% end %}

{% block body %}
<h1>Downcase Filter</h1>

<p>Converts all characters in a string to lowercase.</p>

<h2>Syntax</h2>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{% "string" | downcase %}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>

<h2>Examples</h2>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{% "HELLO" | downcase %}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> hello</p>

<pre><code>{% raw %}
{% "Mixed Case String" | downcase %}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> mixed case string</p>

<pre><code>{% raw %}
{% .title | downcase | truncate: 20 %}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> the lowercased title, truncated to 20 characters</p>
<p>Filters can be chained — <code>downcase</code> runs first, then <code>truncate</code> operates on the result.</p>

<h2>Notes</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Numbers and symbols in the string are passed through unchanged.</li>
  <li>Combine with <code>capitalize</code> to normalize a string: <code>| downcase | capitalize</code>.</li>
</ul>

<h2>See Also</h2>
<ul>
  <li><a href="/docs/filters/capitalize">capitalize</a></li>
  <li><a href="/docs/filters/upcase">upcase</a></li>
</ul>
{% end %}
